<font color="#FF0000">POSITIVE EFFECTS</font><br>
<tt>Tue Oct 21  7:09:20 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
I like the topic of discussion about the positive effects Vietnam Veterans ARE HAVING on society.<br><br>
Recently I had a party and invited 2 Vets whom I met over the Internet. After many of the people went home, 2 of us read, out loud, stories we had written over the years. Our audience was a man and a woman who have been friends of mine since 1979. there was a positive effect because there was *understanding*.<br><br>
Self esteem is important, in that it seemed to be lost (regarding Vietnam service) for many years.<br><br>
Other friends of mine are impressed with the fact that I have a website that deals with Vietnam. There are stories, poetry, humor, and historic documents on this site. This is how we teach others. This is how others learn about self sacrifice. This is how others learn not to judge us by what others (the media) have said or implied - because we are taking an active part! Should we wait for the &quot;benevolent&quot; media to say something nice about us? Hell no! Tell of your experiences, whether they are good or bad, right or wrong. In that way people will know you better. Don't wait for others to do this. It will invariably focus on the negative.<br><br>
Positive effects? Hell yes. I'm glad that there are others who are posting here that feel there is such a possibility.<br><br>
The question should not be whether we are capable of making a difference, the question should be what is taking us so long?<br><br>
Drive on!
<p><code>-- wingman@greene..xtn.net  (Tom Dier) </code><p>


